Design for Smart Living

Beyond Convenience

About The Course

In this studio-based course, students learn core interaction design principles for smart homes, cities, and interconnected lifestyles while critically examining the social, ethical, and human dimensions of technology. They explore diverse frameworks, including Gandhian perspectives on autonomy and resilience, to question whose definitions of “smart” are prioritized and what values are embedded in design. Through hands-on projects and speculative future-casting, students create prototypes and concepts for smart living that are not only technologically innovative but also socially responsible, ethically grounded, and aimed at enhancing human flourishing.

Student Projects

Thematic: Low bandwidth Content Platform Focus: healthcare awareness

Jeeva

Jeeva is a low-bandwidth, offline-first PWA designed to raise awareness about malnutrition and support rural communities with accessible health solution.

Team: Meet Bhatt, Dhyeya Pandya, Darshika Lahoti, Kunal Khandale, Shubham Kumar.

Thematic: Post Language Communication Focus: Ambient Intelligence Systems

The Clique

An offline navigation system in overcrowded areas.

Team: Manasi Vinze, Research and Ethics ,Community Collaborator ,Abhinandit Singh ,Priyansh Jolapara

Thematic: Communication in Communities in Diverse Literacy Levels Focus: Audio-First Interfaces

Raaghir

Raaghir is a voice-first, multilingual digital platform that empowers migrant workers with transparent employer information, community-driven reviews, and direct access to support networks - transforming workplace vulnerability into informed empowerment.

Team: Medha B ,Krishna ,Shriya B ,Vijay Anand ,Gourave Genesh

Thematic: Communication in communities with diverse literacy levels Focus: Visual Communication Systems

Katha

Katha is a storytelling platform where elders record stories and younger ones watch and listen. Over time, it becomes a family archive that preserves stories across generations.

Team: Purva Tekale, Riya Khattri, Keshika Tank, Riddhima Kulkarni, Ananya Bhardwaj

Thematic: Post Language Communication Focus: Gesture-Based Interfaces

Resonate

Resonante lets people communicate using music instead of words, turning conversations into musical phrases.

Team: abhineet Kumar, Gauri Tsering Sharma, Mohak Indulkar, Sania goidani, Rushil Verma

Thematic: shaping communities Focus: privacy on social networks

Privately

A web extension overlay for the privacy of the social media , this extension allows user to access the web social with features like no downloading of post or videos , scanning the page and giving float toggle on screen for the privacy policy and privacy settings

Team: ⁠Zarqa khan, Chaitanya Bodhekar, Riaan shamdasani, Ketki Shroff, Poorva bhombe

Thematic: Privacy-First social networks Focus: Wi-Fi Safety Technology

Safenet

SafeNet provides real-time Wi-Fi security scanning with instant risk assessment and actionable protection solutions. Empowering users to make informed connectivity decisions through real time safety feedback.

Team: Anuja Malu, Shivangi Gajjar, R Sudarshan, Shreya Shinde, Tanishka Vyas, Yusuf Chaiwala
